560
00:29:40,690 --> 00:29:42,940
Then his son and grandson!

561
00:29:43,020 --> 00:29:45,400
It's going to get passed on
through generations.

562
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:48,110
If you do something like this again,

563
00:29:49,110 --> 00:29:51,660
then I'll kill you
no matter the consequences. Got it?

564
00:29:51,740 --> 00:29:53,330
Darn it!

565
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:56,250
Ms. Jin!

566
00:29:56,830 --> 00:29:57,750
Ms. Jin!

567
00:29:58,620 --> 00:29:59,500
Ms. Jin!

568
00:29:59,580 --> 00:30:00,960
This is bad.

569
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:02,710
We're in trouble!

570
00:30:04,630 --> 00:30:05,920
EMERGENCY QUARANTINE
ACCESS CONTROL

571
00:30:07,260 --> 00:30:09,130
EMERGENCY QUARANTINE
DO NOT ENTER

572
00:30:09,220 --> 00:30:10,720
-Goodness.
-My gosh!

573
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,510
-Gosh.
-Goodness.

574
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:14,260
-Goodness.
-How can this happen?

575
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:15,680
What is all this?

576
00:30:16,270 --> 00:30:17,680
PREVENTIVE CULLING OF POTENTIAL
LIVESTOCK WITH FOOT-AND-MOUTH DISEASE

577
00:30:17,770 --> 00:30:19,480
What on earth is happening?

578
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:21,100
Foot-and-mouth disease?

579
00:30:21,190 --> 00:30:23,820
I heard Mr. Kim's goat farm
had an outbreak.

580
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:27,990
Why are the civil servants
headed to the pig farm?

581
00:30:28,070 --> 00:30:32,450
If foot-and-mouth disease breaks out,
cows and pigs within a 3km radius

582
00:30:32,530 --> 00:30:34,830
must be culled by law.

583
00:30:34,910 --> 00:30:35,830
What?

584
00:30:35,910 --> 00:30:39,710
Then Young-soon's pigs will be culled
even though they aren't sick?

585
00:30:39,790 --> 00:30:42,500
That's the law.

586
00:30:42,580 --> 00:30:45,460
Thankfully, Tiger isn't affected.

587
00:30:45,550 --> 00:30:47,260
Damn it!

588
00:30:47,340 --> 00:30:49,420
Who cares about the damn dog right now?

589
00:30:50,010 --> 00:30:51,050
Then…

590
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:53,800
What will happen to that family?

591
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:55,640
For now,

592
00:30:56,850 --> 00:30:58,560
they have to shut down the farm.

593
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:02,810
Those damn goats have been going around
doing all kinds of goat things

594
00:31:02,900 --> 00:31:04,900
all around the village,

595
00:31:04,980 --> 00:31:07,480
and they finally ended up causing trouble.

596
00:31:07,570 --> 00:31:10,360
Goodness.

597
00:31:11,610 --> 00:31:13,780
I feel so bad for Young-soon.

598
00:31:17,910 --> 00:31:21,460
Sir, please don't.
Please don't kill our pigs!

599
00:31:22,420 --> 00:31:24,080
Mom, do something.

600
00:31:24,170 --> 00:31:26,250
Go stop them!

601
00:31:26,790 --> 00:31:28,340
Andrea, please.

602
00:31:28,420 --> 00:31:30,510
Andrea, do something.

603
00:31:39,350 --> 00:31:41,020
Leave her alone!

604
00:31:41,100 --> 00:31:43,310
She's feeding her piglets!

605
00:31:44,060 --> 00:31:45,650
Just leave her there.

606
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:09,050
-Spread out.
-This way.

607
00:32:10,170 --> 00:32:11,840
Be careful.

608
00:32:12,510 --> 00:32:13,590
This way.

609
00:32:17,390 --> 00:32:18,350
Why?

610
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:25,520
Why?!

611
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:30,650
No.

612
00:32:31,820 --> 00:32:33,780
No!

613
00:32:33,860 --> 00:32:35,280
No!

614
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:37,160
No!

615
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:38,530
-Mom.
-Ms. Jin.

616
00:32:38,620 --> 00:32:40,700
-No, stop it, Mom.
-Ms. Jin.

617
00:32:40,790 --> 00:32:41,830
No, Mom.

618
00:32:42,620 --> 00:32:43,790
No.

619
00:32:43,870 --> 00:32:47,750
-You can't do this to them.
-Ms. Jin.

620
00:32:49,090 --> 00:32:52,010
They don't deserve to die like this!

621
00:32:52,090 --> 00:32:53,800
You can't do this to them!

622
00:32:54,380 --> 00:32:56,510
You can't!

623
00:32:56,590 --> 00:32:57,640
No.

624
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:00,930
Those poor things.

625
00:33:01,010 --> 00:33:03,390
Those poor things!

626
00:33:04,140 --> 00:33:07,980
Those poor things!

627
00:33:09,150 --> 00:33:10,360
No!

628
00:33:11,230 --> 00:33:14,530
Those poor things!

629
00:33:14,610 --> 00:33:16,200
-No!
-Don't do that!

630
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:19,780
-Those pigs aren't sick!
-Goodness.

631
00:33:19,870 --> 00:33:23,240
-I can't watch.
-I'm sorry!

632
00:33:23,330 --> 00:33:26,080
Isn't this too harsh?

633
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:27,960
Please be reborn as humans

634
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:30,080
in your next life.

635
00:33:30,170 --> 00:33:33,210
-Goodness.
-Human? Life will be tougher.

636
00:33:33,300 --> 00:33:35,130
-My goodness!
-Hey, Mr. Choi.

637
00:33:35,210 --> 00:33:38,260
I'm glad you called.

638
00:33:38,840 --> 00:33:41,550
Hello. It's me, Sam-sik.

639
00:33:45,180 --> 00:33:46,560
No.

640
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:49,270
I don't have the money yet.

641
00:33:49,350 --> 00:33:50,440
FAIRY BREWERY

642
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:53,480
But if you give me more time,

643
00:33:53,570 --> 00:33:56,780
I'll pay back 200 million won
including interest.

644
00:33:57,360 --> 00:33:59,610
Just one month. I promise you.

645
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:06,040
I promise, I do

646
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:07,210
I do

647
00:34:07,290 --> 00:34:08,660
FAIRY BREWERY, FAIRY REAL ESTATE,
FAIRY FORTUNE TELLING

648
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:11,630
Darn it.

649
00:34:12,670 --> 00:34:15,050
Who the hell drank my alcohol?

650
00:34:15,710 --> 00:34:17,130
I got you, you punk.

651
00:34:17,220 --> 00:34:19,590
What? It's you, Sam-sik.

652
00:34:19,680 --> 00:34:22,550
Goodness, Mr. Yang.

653
00:34:22,640 --> 00:34:25,850
Your security system
is still cutting-edge technology.

654
00:34:25,930 --> 00:34:27,560
I can never steal from your place.

655
00:34:27,640 --> 00:34:28,600
Goodness.

656
00:34:28,680 --> 00:34:31,440
I took a few bottles of makgeolli
to drink with my friends.

657
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:33,560
You can put it under my dad's tab.

658
00:34:33,650 --> 00:34:36,570
Hey, go tell him to pay his tab.

659
00:34:36,650 --> 00:34:37,820
-Okay.
-Hey.

660
00:34:38,490 --> 00:34:42,660
And I put aside those bottles
to use for my ritual tomorrow.

661
00:34:42,740 --> 00:34:44,330
How could you take them?

662
00:34:44,410 --> 00:34:46,950
-All right. Where were we?
-Goodness, that punk.

663
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:49,000
Yes, farming funds.

664
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:54,250
Call the agricultural technology center
to apply for the fund.

665
00:34:54,340 --> 00:34:56,880
-Once you call--
-And listen.

666
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:59,670
Do you know
Kang-ho's family is in big trouble?

667
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:01,130
It's worse than big trouble.

668
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:03,850
That genius became an idiot overnight.

669
00:35:03,930 --> 00:35:04,760
You punk.

670
00:35:04,850 --> 00:35:07,680
Not Kang-ho. I'm talking about the farm.

671
00:35:07,770 --> 00:35:10,140
The poor pigs were all culled

672
00:35:10,230 --> 00:35:14,230
because of the outbreak
of the foot-and-mouth disease.

673
00:35:14,310 --> 00:35:16,230
-What?
-Foot-and-mouth disease?

674
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:18,690
They sacrificed all those pigs

675
00:35:18,780 --> 00:35:20,860
who were squealing
and struggling to survive.

676
00:35:23,660 --> 00:35:25,620
It was painful for me to watch.

677
00:35:26,620 --> 00:35:27,740
Imagine how she felt.

678
00:35:27,830 --> 00:35:30,750
She fed and raised them
like they were her own.

679
00:35:30,830 --> 00:35:32,710
She must be heartbroken.

680
00:35:32,790 --> 00:35:34,500
What about Lion?

681
00:35:35,080 --> 00:35:36,630
Is Lion dead too?

682
00:35:37,250 --> 00:35:38,840
Kang-ho's house

683
00:35:39,460 --> 00:35:42,090
is over 3km away from the goat farm,

684
00:35:42,180 --> 00:35:43,380
so Lion is still alive.

685
00:35:44,010 --> 00:35:45,970
-What a relief.
-What a relief.

686
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:48,470
What's a relief?

687
00:35:48,560 --> 00:35:50,180
This is absurd.

688
00:35:50,680 --> 00:35:52,600
Some had to die

689
00:35:52,690 --> 00:35:54,480
while others lived

690
00:35:55,230 --> 00:35:56,900
by a matter of a few meters.

691
00:35:57,650 --> 00:35:58,610
Goodness.

692
00:36:00,940 --> 00:36:02,990
Thankfully, this one must've survived.

693
00:36:04,610 --> 00:36:07,580
But what's the point?
She lost all the other pigs.

694
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:09,910
She must be very shocked.

695
00:36:10,540 --> 00:36:12,790
She hasn't returned from the farm.

696
00:36:13,580 --> 00:36:14,580
Shut up.

697
00:36:19,050 --> 00:36:20,210
And start searching.

698
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:21,630
Yes, sir.

699
00:36:25,470 --> 00:36:28,100
I don't think it's in here.

700
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:31,220
I don't see any files.
There are just clothes and shoes.

701
00:36:34,020 --> 00:36:36,690
Look, more clothes and shoes.

702
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,360
Mr. So.

703
00:36:52,540 --> 00:36:54,790
Thank you for coming to the family meeting

704
00:36:54,870 --> 00:36:58,710
for our children's wedding
despite your busy schedule.

705
00:36:58,790 --> 00:37:02,960
It's to prepare my dearest daughter
and a great man like him

706
00:37:03,050 --> 00:37:05,880
for their new journey together.

707
00:37:05,970 --> 00:37:09,140
I'd rather miss out on a campaign.

708
00:37:12,310 --> 00:37:16,940
Thank you for considering
my humble son a great man.

709
00:37:17,020 --> 00:37:18,850
I'm very grateful.

710
00:37:18,940 --> 00:37:21,320
We can tell a lot about a person
by their parents.

711
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:23,150
Think of who you are, sir.

712
00:37:23,230 --> 00:37:26,530
You were born into a poor farm,
then later founded Dosang Group,

713
00:37:26,610 --> 00:37:29,780
the top corporation that is
the backbone of our country's economy.

714
00:37:29,870 --> 00:37:33,080
People often tease me,
calling me a rags-to-riches story.

715
00:37:35,750 --> 00:37:36,750
Sir.

716
00:37:36,830 --> 00:37:39,580
That is why I wish
to become the president.

717
00:37:40,250 --> 00:37:42,300
A world where one can rise
from the bottom up.

718
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,380
Nowadays, social injustice
seems permanent,

719
00:37:45,460 --> 00:37:47,510
and wealth and poverty are inherited.

720
00:37:47,590 --> 00:37:49,510
Hence, no one can rise from the bottom up.

721
00:37:50,090 --> 00:37:54,890
That's why the disadvantaged
do not make an effort to grow

722
00:37:54,970 --> 00:37:58,350
and continue to just live
in this hopeless society.

723
00:37:58,890 --> 00:37:59,850
I will

724
00:38:01,110 --> 00:38:05,440
make Korea a place where one can rise.

725
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,240
And

726
00:38:08,820 --> 00:38:10,280
the future of my politics

727
00:38:10,820 --> 00:38:13,410
is you, sir.

728
00:38:31,680 --> 00:38:32,680
Mom.

729
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:35,720
We should go now.

730
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:41,730
Yes.

731
00:38:45,820 --> 00:38:47,860
We should go.

732
00:38:49,780 --> 00:38:51,200
UNGRYEOL AGRICULTURAL CHEMICALS

733
00:38:52,410 --> 00:38:54,080
WHEN NAILS COME

734
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:55,660
Have you heard the news?

735
00:38:55,740 --> 00:38:57,660
About Jou-ri.

736
00:38:57,750 --> 00:38:59,910
I heard it's a huge mess
after the disease outbreak.

737
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,540
Goodness, I heard.

738
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:03,710
I can feel her pain.

739
00:39:03,790 --> 00:39:06,090
We're not talking just one or two pigs.

740
00:39:06,170 --> 00:39:08,510
Where did they bury all those pigs?

741
00:39:08,590 --> 00:39:10,930
The goats were buried
in the yard of the farm,

742
00:39:11,010 --> 00:39:14,720
and the pigs were buried
in the potato field.

743
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:16,350
The potato field?

744
00:39:16,430 --> 00:39:18,310
Then she can't grow potatoes either.

745
00:39:19,060 --> 00:39:20,270
Goodness.

746
00:39:20,350 --> 00:39:21,690
Potatoes?

747
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:23,350
Wait.

748
00:39:23,900 --> 00:39:26,110
Then why did she buy herbicide?

749
00:39:26,190 --> 00:39:27,110
What?

750
00:39:27,730 --> 00:39:28,820
Herbicide?

751
00:39:28,900 --> 00:39:29,820
Yes.

752
00:39:29,900 --> 00:39:32,070
When did she come by to buy it?

753
00:39:32,150 --> 00:39:34,280
As soon as I opened today.

754
00:39:37,830 --> 00:39:39,660
You haven't finished my nails yet!

755
00:39:39,750 --> 00:39:40,870
What…

756
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:43,620
UNGRYEOL AGRICULTURAL CHEMICALS

757
00:39:56,300 --> 00:39:57,260
Kang-ho.

758
00:39:58,010 --> 00:39:59,430
Say hi to your dad.

759
00:40:03,140 --> 00:40:04,150
Dad…

760
00:40:07,190 --> 00:40:08,230
Hello.

761
00:40:16,370 --> 00:40:17,410
Honey.

762
00:40:19,910 --> 00:40:21,620
I brought Kang-ho with me.

763
00:40:22,830 --> 00:40:24,330
I wanted to bring him to you

764
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:27,590
after he starts walking again, but…

765
00:40:30,670 --> 00:40:31,800
I'm sorry.

766
00:40:33,670 --> 00:40:34,760
I'm sorry.

767
00:40:38,510 --> 00:40:41,850
HERE RESTS CHOI HAE-SIK

768
00:40:45,310 --> 00:40:46,310
Mom.

769
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:49,110
Have we picnicked here in the past?

770
00:40:49,690 --> 00:40:51,110
I don't remember.

771
00:40:52,780 --> 00:40:54,820
This is a picnic, right?

772
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:59,450
No, it's not. We need gimbap for a picnic.

773
00:41:06,420 --> 00:41:09,590
My son, this bad mother of yours

774
00:41:10,250 --> 00:41:13,260
never let you go on a picnic
like everyone else.

775
00:41:17,510 --> 00:41:18,590
Long ago,

776
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:22,640
my mom and dad…

777
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:25,680
I mean,

778
00:41:26,520 --> 00:41:29,480
your grandma, grandpa,

779
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:32,020
and uncle…

780
00:41:34,360 --> 00:41:38,030
went on a picnic
with gimbap I made for them

781
00:41:39,910 --> 00:41:41,030
and passed away.

782
00:41:43,540 --> 00:41:44,750
And your dad

783
00:41:45,660 --> 00:41:48,670
also went out with the gimbap I made

784
00:41:49,790 --> 00:41:51,790
and never came back.

785
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:55,510
I was scared of that.

786
00:41:57,170 --> 00:41:58,340
That's why I never let you go.

787
00:42:00,640 --> 00:42:03,260
I was scared by the thought…

788
00:42:05,520 --> 00:42:06,890
of becoming alone again.

789
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:23,330
Mom.

790
00:42:32,080 --> 00:42:33,340
I'll open it for you.

791
00:42:38,380 --> 00:42:41,840
In return, after we drink this,
we have to go down and eat.

792
00:42:42,390 --> 00:42:43,350
I'm hungry.

793
00:42:44,260 --> 00:42:45,930
And what do we do before we eat?

794
00:42:46,020 --> 00:42:47,770
Feed the pigs first.

795
00:42:48,730 --> 00:42:50,270
We have to feed Lion.

796
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:52,900
Lion will grow up,

797
00:42:52,980 --> 00:42:55,110
have piglets, more piglets,

798
00:42:55,190 --> 00:42:56,480
and more.

799
00:42:57,230 --> 00:42:59,780
Then we'll be able to run
our pig farm again, right?

800
00:43:01,950 --> 00:43:03,740
I'll help you out a lot, Mom.

801
00:43:11,580 --> 00:43:12,920
Ms. Jin!

802
00:43:13,000 --> 00:43:14,210
Kang-ho!

803
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:16,170
Are you home?

804
00:43:17,420 --> 00:43:18,710
Ms. Jin!

805
00:43:19,210 --> 00:43:21,010
Look at this. I knew it.

806
00:43:21,090 --> 00:43:23,140
You're here to see Kang-ho because
you heard about the outbreak, right?

807
00:43:23,220 --> 00:43:24,800
Have you seen Ms. Jin and Kang-ho?

808
00:43:24,890 --> 00:43:25,850
They aren't home?

809
00:43:25,930 --> 00:43:28,810
Their farm is closed off now.
Where did they go?

810
00:43:30,850 --> 00:43:32,020
Ms. Jin!

811
00:43:32,100 --> 00:43:33,190
-Kang-ho!
-Hey.

812
00:43:33,270 --> 00:43:34,730
-There they are.
-What?

813
00:43:36,980 --> 00:43:38,690
Hello, Ms. Jin.

814
00:43:39,440 --> 00:43:41,570
I was worried after hearing the news.

815
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:44,200
You must be heartbroken.

816
00:43:44,910 --> 00:43:46,410
UNGRYEOL AGRICULTURAL CHEMICALS

817
00:43:54,040 --> 00:43:55,130
This.

